BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:YKDlTe-tO-kfsJvA9UmYu
SUMMARY:SP 101: Intro to Vera's Screen Print Studio
DTSTAMP:20260307T235948Z
DTSTART:20260312T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 2-hour\, comprehensive hands-on class teaches you all the 
	basics of screen printing at Vera’s shop: From coating and burning a scree
	n\, to pulling your very first print! Get comfortable with Vera's shop lay
	out\, equipment\, and culture. Learn about techniques for creating screens
	\, terminology\, and more to create 1-color projects in the print shop. St
	udents will walk away with the basic skills for screen printing 1-color pa
	per prints\, and their own print of a special Vera design\, specific to th
	e 101 class.\n\nThis class is a prerequisite for other screenprint classes
	 at Vera and access to Open Sessions in Vera's studio. Open Sessions are m
	oderated by members of Vera's Screenprint Committee\, and can provide guid
	ance to participants on their projects. Open Sessions are scheduled for th
	ree times a month in 4 hour intervals. Participants must pay and register 
	for an Open Session in advance on Vera's website.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/
	z4bb5c79181f\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/z4bb5c79181f
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
